text: The Örebro Mission () was a Protestant denomination in Sweden. It was founded in the town of Örebro in 1892 It was part of the Baptist Union of Sweden until 1936. In 1997 the denomination became part of the Evangelical Free Church in Sweden. ==References== Category:1892 establishments in Europe Category:1997 disestablishments in Sweden Category:Protestantism in Sweden Category:Örebro Category:1890s establishments in Sweden
